      <title>Shawl 4 Dwarf Hunting Rules?</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Trade&amp;message.id=12369#M12369</link>
      <description>&lt;div&gt;The first time I did the Shawl, my druid stumbled over Tanik for Shawl 4 almost immediately.  I considered myself lucky, until I found out about 75 crystalline threads.  But that's a different post.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;My 52 enchanter is trying to find Tanik for Shawl 4.  And in a half hour of running around tonight, he encountered neither the poor hurt dwarf, nor the Kromrif Death Squad.  As sucky as my luck has been recently, I would have expected a half hour to be plenty adequate to spawn the KDS and get my high elven derriere punted across the bridge into Iceclad.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;So does anyone happen to remember:&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;. will the dwarf (or the KDS) spawn if you happen to be invisible?&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;. will the dwarf (or the KDS) spawn if you happen to be in an illusion, say a scaled wolf?&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;. do Tanik and the KDS even come to work during the fabled event time?&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;I do know about the charmed rabbit trick, and I'll use it, I guess, next time.  Or a walrus, although personally I think rabbits are cuter than walruses.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Developers - if you're getting some evil idea for a Fabled Kromrif Death Squad, go have a beer instead.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Rowacorn&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Reluctant Heroes&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Bristlebane&lt;/div&gt;</description>
