      <title>Re: Shawl 4 Dwarf Hunting Rules?</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Trade&amp;message.id=12392#M12392</link>
      <description>&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Well, the pet method worked.  I spawned the KDS ten times, and then finally the dwarf.  Things I learned:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;. Enchanter scaled wolf illusion does run faster than the KDS.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;. If you get far enough in front of the KDS, you can camp and come back, you don't always have to zone into Kael.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;. It's really inconvenient when you're about to do the guards at the bottom of the ramp, and that spot turns out to be a KDS spawn spot.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;. You can't charm a snow bunny if it's outfitted with a collector's bunny foot.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;. The KDS doesn't stay charmed.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;So, now I'm faced with the need to raise my tailoring to a fairly high level, and then acquire 5 glowing wurm biles and 75+ crystalline threads.  I think I'll do the tailoring first; anything is better than a hunt in Velks.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Rowacorn&lt;br&gt;Reluctant Heroes&lt;br&gt;Bristlebane&lt;/p&gt;</description>
